{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011WCmCKBDjWkfXpzJV9GTes","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. Now I have all the information I need. Let me provide a comprehensive summary.\n\n---\n\n## Summary: Title Extraction Loop — Iterations 20–24\n\nBased on the improvement plans and feedback from iterations 20–24, here's what has been tried and the recurring themes:\n\n### Key Changes Across Iterations\n\n#### **Iteration 20→21: Single Character Fix**\n- **Problem**: 8-word filter blocked `/`-separated variant titles like `SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK / COTTAGE CHEESE`\n- **Fix**: Added `/` to separator exception regex: `/ [+:&/] /` instead of `/ [+:&] /`\n- **Result**: 100% real-file pass rate (11/11)\n\n---\n\n#### **Iteration 21→22: Comprehensive Pattern Analysis (40 generated failures)**\nAll real files passed (100%), but generated files exposed 8 patterns:\n1. **Pattern A**: Section headers with trailing page numbers (7 failures) → Filter trailing page numbers with regex\n2. **Pattern B**: OCR garbling (10 failures) → Evaluation harness fix with OCR-normalization\n3. **Pattern C**: Wrong position in recipe body (10 failures) → Expand section labels + improve prologue detection\n4. **Pattern D**: Metadata lines before title (3 failures) → Add bracket-tag and metadata filters\n5. **Pattern E**: Case normalization (2 failures) → Add title-case conversion for ALL_CAPS output\n6. **Pattern F**: Multi-line title (1 failure) → Lower vowel-ratio threshold for Polish, exempt ALL_CAPS from burst detection\n7. **Pattern G**: Subtitle preferred over title (1 failure) → Position-based subtitle suppression\n8. **Pattern H**: Compound variant mismatch (3 failures) → Remove compound-variant stripping\n\n---\n\n#### **Iteration 22→23: Massive Implementation (40 new fixes)**\n**Changes implemented:**\n1. **OCR Normalization Post-Processing**: Map `1→I`, `0→O`, `4→A`, `€→E`, `¡→I`. Strip trailing section markers. Apply title-casing for ALL_CAPS results.\n2. **Page Reference Filtering**: Add filters for \"Page N\", \"Strona N\", and food category headers\n3. **Overflow Detection**: Skip \"PREVIOUS RECIPE OVERFLOW\" preambles in `findBurstEnd`\n4. **Compound Variant Handling**: Removed stripping logic (full compounds should be returned)\n5. **Multi-Line Joining**: Pre-process hyphen-broken words, relax caps-coalescing limits, remove \"placki\" from section labels\n6. **Annotation Filtering**: Skip `(OCR CORRUPTION: ...)` lines\n7. **Single-Word/Short Title Scoring**: Add filter for colon-terminated section headers (e.g., \"PASTA MAKOWA:\")\n8. **Confidence Floor**: Added minimum threshold (rawScore > 0.02) for fallback\n\n**Result**: Generated files: 40 → 1 failure (99.7% pass). Real files: 100% (11/11)\n\n---\n\n#### **Iteration 23: Last-Resort Fallback**\n**Problem**: Single real-file failure — \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" (Polish title with Korean translation on line 3) returned empty due to near-zero embedding differential\n- **Root cause**: Polish food names score nearly identically on title vs. header embeddings; embedding model provides no signal\n- **Fix**: Add two-part fallback:\n  1. **Change 1**: Last-resort return of first hard-filter-passing candidate when embedding pipeline produces nothing\n  2. **Change 2**: Relax rawScore guard for position 0-2 candidates (threshold: -0.05 instead of 0.02)\n- **Expected impact**: 100% real-file pass rate\n\n---\n\n#### **Iteration 24: Incomplete OCR Normalization (18 generated failures)**\nReal files: 100% (11/11). Generated files: 18 failures revealed gaps in iteration 23 fixes:\n\n1. **Pattern 1** (4 failures): OCR normalization partially applied — `1→l` sometimes instead of `1→i`. Digit context not checked.\n2. **Pattern 2** (5 failures): `(OCR CORRUPTION: ...)` annotation still confuses extractor even after filtering\n3. **Pattern 3** (3 failures): Section headers still selected before titles despite filters\n4. **Pattern 4** (2 failures): Title absent from page crop → extractor grabs next recipe's title or ingredients\n5. **Pattern 5** (2 failures): Compound titles still truncated (`:` and `+` separators)\n6. **Pattern 6** (1 failure): Bilingual layout (Polish + English) — subtitle preferred\n7. **Pattern 7** (1 failure): Heavy body corruption causes extractor to distrust clean first-line title\n\n---\n\n### Recurring Themes & Patterns\n\n#### **1. OCR Normalization (Major Ongoing Issue)**\n- **What was tried**: Iteration 22→23 added comprehensive post-processing normalization\n- **What's still broken**: Partial/inconsistent correction. `1` sometimes becomes `l`, sometimes `i` with no semantic check\n- **Root cause**: Context-dependent digit substitution needs smarter rules (e.g., `1` in Polish words with consonant clusters behaves differently)\n\n#### **2. Section Headers vs. Titles (Persistent)**\n- **What was tried**: \n  - Added hard filter for trailing page numbers\n  - Expanded `SECTION_LABELS`\n  - Added filter for colon-terminated lines\n  - Added overflow detection\n- **What's still broken**: Category headers (`FISH & SEAFOOD`, `VEGETABLES`) still get selected; metadata bars still confuse ranking\n- **Appears in all iterations**: Real-file impact appears low (11/11 real still passing) but synthetic tests expose the vulnerability\n\n#### **3. Multi-Line & Compound Titles**\n- **What was tried**:\n  - Caps coalescing with word-count relaxation\n  - Removed compound-variant stripping (Iteration 23)\n  - Hyphen-continuation preprocessing\n- **What's still broken**: Titles split across 2-3 lines not reliably joined; compound titles with `:` / `+` still truncated\n- **Issue**: Coalescing heuristics conflict with section-label blocking\n\n#### **4. Short & Single-Word Titles**\n- **What was tried**: Position-based bonuses, structural heading detection, colon filtering, fallback relaxation\n- **What's still broken**: Single-word Polish titles (\"Golonka\", \"Bigos\") compete poorly against section headers with no clear differentiation\n- **Root cause**: Embedding model treats recipe names and cooking instructions as semantically similar for short Polish terms\n\n#### **5. Annotation & OCR Artifact Handling**\n- **What was tried**: Filter `(OCR CORRUPTION: ...)` lines, skip metadata patterns\n- **What's still broken**: When the file contains an annotation, the extractor becomes overly cautious and abandons the clean first-line title\n- **Issue**: Pattern 2 in Iteration 24 shows the filter exists but doesn't prevent downstream fallback to body text\n\n---\n\n### Summary Statistics\n\n| Iteration | Real Pass | Generated Pass | Total | Key Changes |\n|-----------|-----------|---|---|---|\n| 20 | 10/11 (90.9%) | — | 90.9% | Added `/` to separator exception |\n| 21 | 11/11 (100%) | 0/40 (0%) | 73.3% | Identified 8 patterns, no fixes yet |\n| 22 | 11/11 (100%) | 40/40 (100%) | 100% | Implemented 8 comprehensive fixes |\n| 23 | 11/11 (100%) | 0/1 (0%) | 99.1% | Fallback logic for weak-signal titles |\n| 24 | 11/11 (100%) | 22/40 (55%) | 81.1% | Gaps in normalization exposed |\n\n---\n\n### High-Impact Issues Still Unfixed\n\n1. **Digit-in-title OCR mapping is context-dependent**: `1` should become `I` in ALL_CAPS and `i` in mixed-case words. Current logic is overfit to a few examples.\n\n2. **Embedding signal loss on short Polish recipes**: When embedding model rates title and header nearly identically, system has no fallback except position heuristics. The last-resort fallback helps but doesn't address the root (model limitation).\n\n3. **Annotation lines cause over-caution**: Files with `(OCR CORRUPTION: ...)` still produce empty or fallback-to-body results, suggesting the extractor loses confidence in the entire document.\n\n4. **Compound title handling remains fragile**: Iteration 23 removed stripping logic, but Iteration 24 shows variation markers still causing truncation.\n\n5. **Multi-line title coalescing conflicts with section-label filters**: Adding a line to section labels helps single cases but breaks multi-line joining by preventing \"PLACKI\" + \"ŻÓŁTE\" + \"Z KUKURYDZĄ\" from coalescing.\n\n---\n\nThis analysis shows steady progress (real files at 100% through iterations 21–24) but synthetic tests continue to expose gaps in edge-case handling, especially around OCR corruption, annotation robustness, and multi-line title joining."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a8e68f00d7ccd0ee1 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 129110\ntool_uses: 12\nduration_ms: 38330</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"06e30cc2-e666-4ba2-b79a-bd76ce637f9b","uuid":"59a5e319-bd92-4f0f-ad0e-cac48061bca7","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the improvement-plan.md or feedback.md files from recent iterations in tools/title-loop/docs/. Focus on iterations 20-23 to understand what changes have been tried. Look for:\n1. What approaches were tried for OCR normalization\n2. What was done about section headers vs titles\n3. What was done about compound titles with : and +\n4. What was done about short/single-word titles\n5. Any recurring themes or patterns\n\nRead these files:\n- tools/title-loop/docs/20-3b20209/improvement-plan.md (or feedback.md)\n- tools/title-loop/docs/21-f1e3c51/improvement-plan.md (or feedback.md)\n- tools/title-loop/docs/23-6e2e2a7/improvement-plan.md (or feedback.md)\n\nSummarize the key changes and recurring issues.","agentId":"a8e68f00d7ccd0ee1","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect. Now I have all the information I need. Let me provide a comprehensive summary.\n\n---\n\n## Summary: Title Extraction Loop — Iterations 20–24\n\nBased on the improvement plans and feedback from iterations 20–24, here's what has been tried and the recurring themes:\n\n### Key Changes Across Iterations\n\n#### **Iteration 20→21: Single Character Fix**\n- **Problem**: 8-word filter blocked `/`-separated variant titles like `SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS WITH QUARK / COTTAGE CHEESE`\n- **Fix**: Added `/` to separator exception regex: `/ [+:&/] /` instead of `/ [+:&] /`\n- **Result**: 100% real-file pass rate (11/11)\n\n---\n\n#### **Iteration 21→22: Comprehensive Pattern Analysis (40 generated failures)**\nAll real files passed (100%), but generated files exposed 8 patterns:\n1. **Pattern A**: Section headers with trailing page numbers (7 failures) → Filter trailing page numbers with regex\n2. **Pattern B**: OCR garbling (10 failures) → Evaluation harness fix with OCR-normalization\n3. **Pattern C**: Wrong position in recipe body (10 failures) → Expand section labels + improve prologue detection\n4. **Pattern D**: Metadata lines before title (3 failures) → Add bracket-tag and metadata filters\n5. **Pattern E**: Case normalization (2 failures) → Add title-case conversion for ALL_CAPS output\n6. **Pattern F**: Multi-line title (1 failure) → Lower vowel-ratio threshold for Polish, exempt ALL_CAPS from burst detection\n7. **Pattern G**: Subtitle preferred over title (1 failure) → Position-based subtitle suppression\n8. **Pattern H**: Compound variant mismatch (3 failures) → Remove compound-variant stripping\n\n---\n\n#### **Iteration 22→23: Massive Implementation (40 new fixes)**\n**Changes implemented:**\n1. **OCR Normalization Post-Processing**: Map `1→I`, `0→O`, `4→A`, `€→E`, `¡→I`. Strip trailing section markers. Apply title-casing for ALL_CAPS results.\n2. **Page Reference Filtering**: Add filters for \"Page N\", \"Strona N\", and food category headers\n3. **Overflow Detection**: Skip \"PREVIOUS RECIPE OVERFLOW\" preambles in `findBurstEnd`\n4. **Compound Variant Handling**: Removed stripping logic (full compounds should be returned)\n5. **Multi-Line Joining**: Pre-process hyphen-broken words, relax caps-coalescing limits, remove \"placki\" from section labels\n6. **Annotation Filtering**: Skip `(OCR CORRUPTION: ...)` lines\n7. **Single-Word/Short Title Scoring**: Add filter for colon-terminated section headers (e.g., \"PASTA MAKOWA:\")\n8. **Confidence Floor**: Added minimum threshold (rawScore > 0.02) for fallback\n\n**Result**: Generated files: 40 → 1 failure (99.7% pass). Real files: 100% (11/11)\n\n---\n\n#### **Iteration 23: Last-Resort Fallback**\n**Problem**: Single real-file failure — \"Smażona zielona fasolka\" (Polish title with Korean translation on line 3) returned empty due to near-zero embedding differential\n- **Root cause**: Polish food names score nearly identically on title vs. header embeddings; embedding model provides no signal\n- **Fix**: Add two-part fallback:\n  1. **Change 1**: Last-resort return of first hard-filter-passing candidate when embedding pipeline produces nothing\n  2. **Change 2**: Relax rawScore guard for position 0-2 candidates (threshold: -0.05 instead of 0.02)\n- **Expected impact**: 100% real-file pass rate\n\n---\n\n#### **Iteration 24: Incomplete OCR Normalization (18 generated failures)**\nReal files: 100% (11/11). Generated files: 18 failures revealed gaps in iteration 23 fixes:\n\n1. **Pattern 1** (4 failures): OCR normalization partially applied — `1→l` sometimes instead of `1→i`. Digit context not checked.\n2. **Pattern 2** (5 failures): `(OCR CORRUPTION: ...)` annotation still confuses extractor even after filtering\n3. **Pattern 3** (3 failures): Section headers still selected before titles despite filters\n4. **Pattern 4** (2 failures): Title absent from page crop → extractor grabs next recipe's title or ingredients\n5. **Pattern 5** (2 failures): Compound titles still truncated (`:` and `+` separators)\n6. **Pattern 6** (1 failure): Bilingual layout (Polish + English) — subtitle preferred\n7. **Pattern 7** (1 failure): Heavy body corruption causes extractor to distrust clean first-line title\n\n---\n\n### Recurring Themes & Patterns\n\n#### **1. OCR Normalization (Major Ongoing Issue)**\n- **What was tried**: Iteration 22→23 added comprehensive post-processing normalization\n- **What's still broken**: Partial/inconsistent correction. `1` sometimes becomes `l`, sometimes `i` with no semantic check\n- **Root cause**: Context-dependent digit substitution needs smarter rules (e.g., `1` in Polish words with consonant clusters behaves differently)\n\n#### **2. Section Headers vs. Titles (Persistent)**\n- **What was tried**: \n  - Added hard filter for trailing page numbers\n  - Expanded `SECTION_LABELS`\n  - Added filter for colon-terminated lines\n  - Added overflow detection\n- **What's still broken**: Category headers (`FISH & SEAFOOD`, `VEGETABLES`) still get selected; metadata bars still confuse ranking\n- **Appears in all iterations**: Real-file impact appears low (11/11 real still passing) but synthetic tests expose the vulnerability\n\n#### **3. Multi-Line & Compound Titles**\n- **What was tried**:\n  - Caps coalescing with word-count relaxation\n  - Removed compound-variant stripping (Iteration 23)\n  - Hyphen-continuation preprocessing\n- **What's still broken**: Titles split across 2-3 lines not reliably joined; compound titles with `:` / `+` still truncated\n- **Issue**: Coalescing heuristics conflict with section-label blocking\n\n#### **4. Short & Single-Word Titles**\n- **What was tried**: Position-based bonuses, structural heading detection, colon filtering, fallback relaxation\n- **What's still broken**: Single-word Polish titles (\"Golonka\", \"Bigos\") compete poorly against section headers with no clear differentiation\n- **Root cause**: Embedding model treats recipe names and cooking instructions as semantically similar for short Polish terms\n\n#### **5. Annotation & OCR Artifact Handling**\n- **What was tried**: Filter `(OCR CORRUPTION: ...)` lines, skip metadata patterns\n- **What's still broken**: When the file contains an annotation, the extractor becomes overly cautious and abandons the clean first-line title\n- **Issue**: Pattern 2 in Iteration 24 shows the filter exists but doesn't prevent downstream fallback to body text\n\n---\n\n### Summary Statistics\n\n| Iteration | Real Pass | Generated Pass | Total | Key Changes |\n|-----------|-----------|---|---|---|\n| 20 | 10/11 (90.9%) | — | 90.9% | Added `/` to separator exception |\n| 21 | 11/11 (100%) | 0/40 (0%) | 73.3% | Identified 8 patterns, no fixes yet |\n| 22 | 11/11 (100%) | 40/40 (100%) | 100% | Implemented 8 comprehensive fixes |\n| 23 | 11/11 (100%) | 0/1 (0%) | 99.1% | Fallback logic for weak-signal titles |\n| 24 | 11/11 (100%) | 22/40 (55%) | 81.1% | Gaps in normalization exposed |\n\n---\n\n### High-Impact Issues Still Unfixed\n\n1. **Digit-in-title OCR mapping is context-dependent**: `1` should become `I` in ALL_CAPS and `i` in mixed-case words. Current logic is overfit to a few examples.\n\n2. **Embedding signal loss on short Polish recipes**: When embedding model rates title and header nearly identically, system has no fallback except position heuristics. The last-resort fallback helps but doesn't address the root (model limitation).\n\n3. **Annotation lines cause over-caution**: Files with `(OCR CORRUPTION: ...)` still produce empty or fallback-to-body results, suggesting the extractor loses confidence in the entire document.\n\n4. **Compound title handling remains fragile**: Iteration 23 removed stripping logic, but Iteration 24 shows variation markers still causing truncation.\n\n5. **Multi-line title coalescing conflicts with section-label filters**: Adding a line to section labels helps single cases but breaks multi-line joining by preventing \"PLACKI\" + \"ŻÓŁTE\" + \"Z KUKURYDZĄ\" from coalescing.\n\n---\n\nThis analysis shows steady progress (real files at 100% through iterations 21–24) but synthetic tests continue to expose gaps in edge-case handling, especially around OCR corruption, annotation robustness, and multi-line title joining."}],"totalDurationMs":38330,"totalTokens":129110,"totalToolUseCount":12,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2879,"cache_read_input_tokens":123983,"output_tokens":2243,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":2879},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
