{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LDBzGsVNoFideiajXuiTam","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Reduce heat and stir in the remaining stock, one ladle at a time, until the rice is\n     2→creamy but still al dente, about 18-20 minutes. The risotto should flow slightly on the plate.\n     3→Season with salt and white pepper. Finish with butter and grated Parmigiano-Reggiano.\n     4→\n     5→CARPACCIO DI PESCE SPADA\n     6→\n     7→Slice the swordfish paper-thin. Arrange on chilled plates. Dress with extra virgin olive oil,\n     8→lemon juice, and sea salt. Scatter thinly shaved fennel and microgreens. Serve immediately.\n     9→\n    10→Preparation: 10 minutes\n    11→Serves: 4\n    12→\n    13→CARPACCIO WITH CITRUS DRESSING\n    14→\n    15→Place thin slices on a cold plate. Whisk together lemon, lime, orange juice with good quality\n    16→oil. Season with fıne sea salt and crushed coriander seeds. Garnish with fresh herbs and\n    17→thinly sliced radish.\n    18→\n    19→nto a loured work counter and knead until smooth, approx 8 minutes. Proof in oiled bowl, cover\n    20→with damp cloth, 45 minutes at room temperature. Shape into ½ dozen rounds. Second proof 30 min.\n    21→\n    22→Place pans in 225°C/435-VI0.. oven for 12-15 minutes until golden brown. Cool on wire rack.\n    23→\n    24→Makes: 1 dozen\n    25→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"06e30cc2-e666-4ba2-b79a-bd76ce637f9b","uuid":"73e19532-2496-4cad-a4ea-dc3829777787","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Mushroom Risotto.generated.txt","content":"Reduce heat and stir in the remaining stock, one ladle at a time, until the rice is\ncreamy but still al dente, about 18-20 minutes. The risotto should flow slightly on the plate.\nSeason with salt and white pepper. Finish with butter and grated Parmigiano-Reggiano.\n\nCARPACCIO DI PESCE SPADA\n\nSlice the swordfish paper-thin. Arrange on chilled plates. Dress with extra virgin olive oil,\nlemon juice, and sea salt. Scatter thinly shaved fennel and microgreens. Serve immediately.\n\nPreparation: 10 minutes\nServes: 4\n\nCARPACCIO WITH CITRUS DRESSING\n\nPlace thin slices on a cold plate. Whisk together lemon, lime, orange juice with good quality\noil. Season with fıne sea salt and crushed coriander seeds. Garnish with fresh herbs and\nthinly sliced radish.\n\nnto a loured work counter and knead until smooth, approx 8 minutes. Proof in oiled bowl, cover\nwith damp cloth, 45 minutes at room temperature. Shape into ½ dozen rounds. Second proof 30 min.\n\nPlace pans in 225°C/435-VI0.. oven for 12-15 minutes until golden brown. Cool on wire rack.\n\nMakes: 1 dozen\n","numLines":25,"startLine":1,"totalLines":64}}}
