{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01J8w82iHQSHVQyvqfEdZpUH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→Golonka\n     2→Roasted Pork Knuckle\n     3→\n     4→Ingredients:\n     5→- 2 pork knuckles (about 3-4 lbs each)\n     6→- 2 tablespoons caraway seeds\n     7→- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n     8→- 2 tablespoons Dijon mustard\n     9→- 2 tablespoons honey\n    10→- 2 tablespoons soy sauce\n    11→- 1 tablespoon paprika\n    12→- 1 teaspoon marjoram\n    13→- Salt and pepper to taste\n    14→- 2 cups beef or pork stock\n    15→- 2 cups root vegetables (carrots, parsnips, onions)\n    16→- 2 bay leaves\n    17→- 1 tablespoon cornstarch\n    18→- 3 tablespoons water\n    19→\n    20→Instructions:\n    21→\n    22→Preparation:\n    23→Score the skin of pork knuckles in crosshatch pattern.\n    24→Pat dry with paper towels.\n    25→\n    26→Marinade:\n    27→Combine mustard, honey, soy sauce, paprika, marjoram in bowl.\n    28→Mix in minced garlic and caraway seeds.\n    29→Rub mixture all over knuckles.\n    30→Season generously with salt and pepper.\n    31→Let marinate at room temperature for 30 minutes.\n    32→\n    33→Roasting:\n    34→Preheat oven to 325°F.\n    35→Place knuckles in roasting pan skin side up.\n    36→Pour stock around the meat.\n    37→Scatter vegetables around pan.\n    38→Add bay leaves.\n    39→Roast for 2.5 to 3 hours, basting every 30 minutes.\n    40→Internal temperature should reach 165°F.\n    41→\n    42→Sauce:\n    43→Remove knuckles and vegetables from pan.\n    44→Skim fat from pan juices.\n    45→Mix cornstarch with water.\n    46→Heat pan juices on stovetop, whisk in cornstarch slurry.\n    47→Simmer 2-3 minutes until thickened.\n    48→Strain and serve with meat.\n    49→\n    50→Serving: Slice meat thinly, serve with pan sauce and vegetables.\n    51→\n    52→Serves: 6-8 people\n    53→Prep time: 20 minutes\n    54→Cooking time: 3 hours"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"06e30cc2-e666-4ba2-b79a-bd76ce637f9b","uuid":"961d479b-fe8b-4dbe-904e-9767cef53c1c","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Golonka.generated.txt","content":"Golonka\nRoasted Pork Knuckle\n\nIngredients:\n- 2 pork knuckles (about 3-4 lbs each)\n- 2 tablespoons caraway seeds\n- 4 cloves garlic, minced\n- 2 tablespoons Dijon mustard\n- 2 tablespoons honey\n- 2 tablespoons soy sauce\n- 1 tablespoon paprika\n- 1 teaspoon marjoram\n- Salt and pepper to taste\n- 2 cups beef or pork stock\n- 2 cups root vegetables (carrots, parsnips, onions)\n- 2 bay leaves\n- 1 tablespoon cornstarch\n- 3 tablespoons water\n\nInstructions:\n\nPreparation:\nScore the skin of pork knuckles in crosshatch pattern.\nPat dry with paper towels.\n\nMarinade:\nCombine mustard, honey, soy sauce, paprika, marjoram in bowl.\nMix in minced garlic and caraway seeds.\nRub mixture all over knuckles.\nSeason generously with salt and pepper.\nLet marinate at room temperature for 30 minutes.\n\nRoasting:\nPreheat oven to 325°F.\nPlace knuckles in roasting pan skin side up.\nPour stock around the meat.\nScatter vegetables around pan.\nAdd bay leaves.\nRoast for 2.5 to 3 hours, basting every 30 minutes.\nInternal temperature should reach 165°F.\n\nSauce:\nRemove knuckles and vegetables from pan.\nSkim fat from pan juices.\nMix cornstarch with water.\nHeat pan juices on stovetop, whisk in cornstarch slurry.\nSimmer 2-3 minutes until thickened.\nStrain and serve with meat.\n\nServing: Slice meat thinly, serve with pan sauce and vegetables.\n\nServes: 6-8 people\nPrep time: 20 minutes\nCooking time: 3 hours","numLines":54,"startLine":1,"totalLines":54}}}
