{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01BCMYQHJQAkJHbuiZgPZkGs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The improvement plan is written. Here's a brief overview of the key proposals:\n\n**The big architectural change**: Move OCR repair *before* candidate scoring instead of after. A dictionary-guided repair function (~500 food words) resolves ambiguous digit→letter substitutions (`1→l` vs `1→i`) by checking which substitution produces a real word. This fixes Patterns 1, 2, and 7 (10 of 18 failures).\n\n**Structural fixes**:\n- **Pattern 3** (3 failures): Switch position bonus from raw-line-position to candidate-relative-position, so the first candidate after filtered preamble lines (category headers, metadata) gets proper priority.\n- **Pattern 4** (2 failures): Detect title-absent pages (first 3 lines are all ingredients/instructions) and return empty instead of guessing.\n- **Pattern 5** (2 failures): Protect compound titles (containing ` : ` or ` + `) from the \"shorter substring wins\" dedup rule.\n- **Pattern 6** (1 failure): Detect bilingual layout pattern (short title + English subtitle + Ingredients:) and boost the short title. Also expand the cooking-verb filter list."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7468,"cache_read_input_tokens":73344,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":7468},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"06e30cc2-e666-4ba2-b79a-bd76ce637f9b","uuid":"5ce874a3-1a74-4ce7-ac91-fffefc0a79e2"}
